",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PZxgp9MguMgByiwZUmZxut\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\n    \\\"scan_id\\\": \\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\n    \\\"project_id\\\": \\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\n    \\\"scan_type\\\": \\\"observability_scout\\\",\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"code_quality\\\",\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Add error handling to maintainCache() timer\\\",\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"TenantKeyManager.maintainCache() runs on a 60-second interval and awaits Promise.all() for key derivations, but has no try/catch. If any derivation throws, the rejected promise is unobserved — Node.js emits unhandledRejection and the maintenance cycle silently stops working. Wrap the method body in try/catch, log the error with context (which tenantId failed, how many succeeded), and ensure the timer continues for the next cycle.\\\",\\n    \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"Silent maintenance timer failures are insidious — the cache appears to work but keys gradually expire without renewal, eventually causing a burst of synchronous derivations under load. This is exactly the kind of failure that surfaces as a mysterious latency spike during peak traffic. A simple try/catch with structured logging prevents this entire failure mode.\\\",\\n    \\\"effort\\\": 1,\\n    \\\"impact\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"risk\\\": 1\\n  }'\",\"description\":\"Save idea 4\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1000,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45630,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1000},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\