ails at 3 AM, the raw error message gives zero clues about which tenant or credential is affected. Structured DecryptionError with context fields enables instant triage. PBKDF2 timing helps detect CPU contention before it causes cascading latency.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":2,\\\"impact\\\":8,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:38.484Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:38.484Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":2,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"5e90e7b9-1855-4475-aed1-dd66a38f48d6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:38.511Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"9d94bcf2-560c-4af8-9df6-26d778adafe1\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"code_quality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Wrap decrypt() with DecryptionError and timing\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The decrypt() function in crypto.ts throws raw Node.js crypto errors with no operational context. The DecryptionError class already exists but is never used by decrypt() itself. Wrap decrypt() to catch crypto failures and re-throw as DecryptionError with tenantId, credentialId, and resourceType context. Additionally, instrument deriveTenantKey/deriveTenantKeyAsync with timing logs so operators can spot PBKDF2 slowdowns.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"When decryption fails at 3 AM, the raw error message gives zero clues about which tenant or credential is affected. Structured DecryptionError with context fields enables instant triage. PBKDF2 timing helps detect CPU contention before it causes cascading latency.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":2,\\\"impact\\\":8,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:38.484Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:38.484Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":2,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:41.858Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PZgyPWnsf1GEqYRHsYhqNK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"That works. Now saving the remaining 4 ideas.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1000,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45630,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1000},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"ff58a75d-6cd4-4f88-92e7-ef52b797e601\"}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:44.565Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PZgyPWnsf1GEqYRHsYhqNK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01F1RYngSdAYwNykGMyETuFc\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\n    \\\"scan_id\\\": \\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\n    \\\"project_id\\\": \\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\n    \\\"scan_type\\\": \\\"observability_scout\\\",\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"functionality\\\",\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Add cache hit/miss metrics to TenantKeyManager\\\",\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"TenantKeyManager.getKey() silently serves from cache or derives a new key with no visibility into the ratio. Add hit/miss counters and expose them via a getMetrics() method returning {hits, misses, cacheSize, derivations, avgDerivationMs}. Log a periodic summary at info level during maintainCache() so operators can see cache effectiveness without polling.\\\",\\n    \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"The key cache is a critical performance optimization — PBKDF2 with 100k iterations is expensive. Without hit/miss tracking, operators cannot tell if the cache is effective, if the TTL is too aggressive, or if thundering herd derivations are causing latency spikes. These metrics are cheap to collect and immediately actionable.\\\",\\n    \\\"effort\\\": 3,\\n    \\\"impact\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"risk\\\": 1\\n  }'\",\"description\":\"Save idea 2\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1000,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45630,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1000},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"567bd183-74e1-404b-8e93-2579c71ef52b\"}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:47.644Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01F1RYngSdAYwNykGMyETuFc\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"a6fb84a4-fc47-4b17-b63b-2d723d6fd071\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"functionality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Add cache hit/miss metrics to TenantKeyManager\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"TenantKeyManager.getKey() silently serves from cache or derives a new key with no visibility into the ratio. Add hit/miss counters and expose them via a getMetrics() method returning {hits, misses, cacheSize, derivations, avgDerivationMs}. Log a periodic summary at info level during maintainCache() so operators can see cache effectiveness without polling.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"The key cache is a critical performance optimization � PBKDF2 with 100k iterations is expensive. Without hit/miss tracking, operators cannot tell if the cache is effective, if the TTL is too aggressive, or if thundering herd derivations are causing latency spikes. These metrics are cheap to collect and immediately actionable.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":3,\\\"impact\\\":7,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:47.051Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:47.051Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":1,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"2e023903-4109-4272-b831-a28c7ba2250d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:47.067Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"a6fb84a4-fc47-4b17-b63b-2d723d6fd071\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"functionality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Add cache hit/miss metrics to TenantKeyManager\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"TenantKeyManager.getKey() silently serves from cache or derives a new key with no visibility into the ratio. Add hit/miss counters and expose them via a getMetrics() method returning {hits, misses, cacheSize, derivations, avgDerivationMs}. Log a periodic summary at info level during maintainCache() so operators can see cache effectiveness without polling.