lifecycle.\\\",\\n    \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"For any system handling encrypted secrets, the full credential lifecycle must be auditable. An attacker or rogue admin could delete credentials to cover tracks, and the current code would leave zero evidence. The audit infrastructure already exists; the gap is just missing call sites at deletion and access endpoints.\\\",\\n    \\\"effort\\\": 2,\\n    \\\"impact\\\": 9,\\n    \\\"risk\\\": 2\\n  }'\",\"description\":\"Save idea 3\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1000,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45630,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1000},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"abe27651-9782-41e4-b922-3ef6d0d6322d\"}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:50.407Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01WUokAmrkPrBMMWS6rX6ag8\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"5ed3fcb2-72b2-42a9-9bfd-a11c9bb472f9\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"code_quality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Audit credential deletion and access operations\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Only credential creation (key:encrypt) produces an audit log entry in httpApi.ts. Credential deletion (DELETE /api/credentials/:id) and credential listing for a persona (GET /api/personas/:id/credentials) leave no audit trail. Add auditLog.record() calls for key:delete and key:access actions at those endpoints, including the tenantId and resourceId. This closes a compliance-critical gap in the credential lifecycle.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"For any system handling encrypted secrets, the full credential lifecycle must be auditable. An attacker or rogue admin could delete credentials to cover tracks, and the current code would leave zero evidence. The audit infrastructure already exists; the gap is just missing call sites at deletion and access endpoints.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":2,\\\"impact\\\":9,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.160Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.160Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":2,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"bbad5cab-252d-4cc8-819a-efda97904032\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.177Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"5ed3fcb2-72b2-42a9-9bfd-a11c9bb472f9\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"code_quality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Audit credential deletion and access operations\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Only credential creation (key:encrypt) produces an audit log entry in httpApi.ts. Credential deletion (DELETE /api/credentials/:id) and credential listing for a persona (GET /api/personas/:id/credentials) leave no audit trail. Add auditLog.record() calls for key:delete and key:access actions at those endpoints, including the tenantId and resourceId. This closes a compliance-critical gap in the credential lifecycle.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"For any system handling encrypted secrets, the full credential lifecycle must be auditable. An attacker or rogue admin could delete credentials to cover tracks, and the current code would leave zero evidence. The audit infrastructure already exists; the gap is just missing call sites at deletion and access endpoints.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":2,\\\"impact\\\":9,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.160Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:50.160Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":2,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:50.757Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PZgyPWnsf1GEqYRHsYhqNK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PZxgp9MguMgByiwZUmZxut\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\n    \\\"scan_id\\\": \\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\n    \\\"project_id\\\": \\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\n    \\\"scan_type\\\": \\\"observability_scout\\\",\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"code_quality\\\",\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Add error handling to maintainCache() timer\\\",\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"TenantKeyManager.maintainCache() runs on a 60-second interval and awaits Promise.all() for key derivations, but has no try/catch. If any derivation throws, the rejected promise is unobserved — Node.js emits unhandledRejection and the maintenance cycle silently stops working. Wrap the method body in try/catch, log the error with context (which tenantId failed, how many succeeded), and ensure the timer continues for the next cycle.\\\",\\n    \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"Silent maintenance timer failures are insidious — the cache appears to work but keys gradually expire without renewal, eventually causing a burst of synchronous derivations under load. This is exactly the kind of failure that surfaces as a mysterious latency spike during peak traffic. A simple try/catch with structured logging prevents this entire failure mode.\\\",\\n    \\\"effort\\\": 1,\\n    \\\"impact\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"risk\\\": 1\\n  }'\",\"description\":\"Save idea 4\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1000,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45630,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1000},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"fe79b66b-a317-439b-a397-dce75aa522cb\"}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:53.418Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PZxgp9MguMgByiwZUmZxut\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"b5669bc2-0e2c-49c2-bad6-f66d674bc9eb\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"code_quality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Add error handling to maintainCache() timer\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"TenantKeyManager.maintainCache() runs on a 60-second interval and awaits Promise.all() for key derivations, but has no try/catch. If any derivation throws, the rejected promise is unobserved � Node.js emits unhandledRejection and the maintenance cycle silently stops working. Wrap the method body in try/catch, log the error with context (which tenantId failed, how many succeeded), and ensure the timer continues for the next cycle.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"Silent maintenance timer failures are insidious � the cache appears to work but keys gradually expire without renewal, eventually causing a burst of synchronous derivations under load. This is exactly the kind of failure that surfaces as a mysterious latency spike during peak traffic. A simple try/catch with structured logging prevents this entire failure mode.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":1,\\\"impact\\\":7,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:53.142Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:53.142Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":1,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"bf0c6d92-c1d9-492f-aef1-5c1c3ecfb470\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:53.160Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"b5669bc2-0e2c-49c2-bad6-f66d674bc9eb\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"code_quality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Add error handling to maintainCache() timer\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"TenantKeyManager.maintainCache() runs on a 60-second interval and awaits Promise.all() for key derivations, but has no try/catch. If any derivation throws, the rejected promise is unobserved � Node.js emits unhandledRejection and the maintenance cycle silently stops working. Wrap the method body in try/catch, log the error with context (which tenantId failed, how many succeeded), and ensure the timer continues for the next cycle.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"Silent maintenance timer failures are insidious � the cache appears to work but keys gradually expire without renewal, eventually causing a burst of synchronous derivations under load. This is exactly the kind of failure that surfaces as a mysterious latency spike during peak traffic. A simple try/catch with structured logging prevents this entire failure mode.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":1,\\\"impact\\\":7,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:53.142Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:53.142Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":1,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:53.481Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01PZgyPWnsf1GEqYRHsYhqNK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01L5BdYAbxy2Xyhy1ZCg5W3g\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\n    \\\"scan_id\\\": \\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\n    \\\"project_id\\\": \\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\n    \\\"scan_type\\\": \\\"observability_scout\\\",\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"functionality\\\",\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Expose credential file gauge and cleanup metrics\\\",\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"The credentialInjector module tracks active credential files in a Set but never exposes the count. Add an exported getActiveCredentialFileCount() function and log the gauge at info level during sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles(). Also log when the exit handler fires with the count of files it attempted to clean and whether each unlink succeeded. This surfaces credential file leaks before they exhaust /dev/shm space.\\\",\\n    \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"Credential files on /dev/shm are the most security-sensitive temp artifacts in the system. If cleanup fails silently (which the current catch blocks allow), credentials persist on disk indefinitely. A simple gauge metric lets operators detect the leak pattern — monotonically increasing active file count — before it becomes a security incident or disk exhaustion.\\\",\\n    \\\"effort\\\": 2,\\n    \\\"impact\\\": 6,\\n    \\\"risk\\\": 1\\n  }'\",\"description\":\"Save idea 5\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1000,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":45630,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1000},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"cd820218-7182-4450-9848-96fab187a50b\"}\n[2026-03-18T11:53:56.394Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01L5BdYAbxy2Xyhy1ZCg5W3g\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"8dd7bb19-1e4a-479d-9e1b-ec6094113980\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"functionality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Expose credential file gauge and cleanup metrics\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The credentialInjector module tracks active credential files in a Set but never exposes the count. Add an exported getActiveCredentialFileCount() function and log the gauge at info level during sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles(). Also log when the exit handler fires with the count of files it attempted to clean and whether each unlink succeeded. This surfaces credential file leaks before they exhaust /dev/shm space.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"Credential files on /dev/shm are the most security-sensitive temp artifacts in the system. If cleanup fails silently (which the current catch blocks allow), credentials persist on disk indefinitely. A simple gauge metric lets operators detect the leak pattern � monotonically increasing active file count � before it becomes a security incident or disk exhaustion.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":2,\\\"impact\\\":6,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:56.304Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:56.304Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":1,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"6b375ece-41c0-48fe-9151-de360e723e96\",\"uuid\":\"0a72027e-8fe5-49dc-94ec-ed000d4113ea\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T11:53:56.320Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"idea\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"8dd7bb19-1e4a-479d-9e1b-ec6094113980\\\",\\\"scan_id\\\":\\\"0e5ab481-52cf-45a9-aeb0-f04397a63a1b\\\",\\\"project_id\\\":\\\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\\\",\\\"context_id\\\":null,\\\"scan_type\\\":\\\"observability_scout\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"functionality\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Expose credential file gauge and cleanup metrics\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"The credentialInjector module tracks active credential files in a Set but never exposes the count. Add an exported getActiveCredentialFileCount() function and log the gauge at info level during sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles(). Also log when the exit handler fires with the count of files it attempted to clean and whether each unlink succeeded. This surfaces credential file leaks before they exhaust /dev/shm space.\\\",\\\"reasoning\\\":\\\"Credential files on /dev/shm are the most security-sensitive temp artifacts in the system. If cleanup fails silently (which the current catch blocks allow), credentials persist on disk indefinitely. A simple gauge metric lets operators detect the leak pattern � monotonically increasing active file count � before it becomes a security incident or disk exhaustion.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\",\\\"user_feedback\\\":null,\\\"user_pattern\\\":0,\\\"effort\\\":2,\\\"impact\\\":6,\\\"implemented_at\\\":null,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:56.304Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-03-18T11:53:56.304Z\\\",\\\"requirement_id\\\":null,\\\"goal_id\\\":null,\\\"risk\\\":1,\\\"provider\\\":null,\\\"model\\\":null,\\\"detailed\\\":0}}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n[2026-03-18T11:54:05.327Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Dv9ScUu9wEgVuCJNyWdTMV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"All 5 ideas saved successfully. Here's the summary:\\n\\n## Observability Scout - Credential & Secret Management\\n\\n**5 ideas created** for the \\\"Credential & Secret Management\\\" context:\\n\\n| # | Title | Category | Effort | Impact | Risk |\\n|---|-------|----------|--------|--------|------|\\n| 1 | Wrap decrypt() with DecryptionError and timing | code_quality | 2 | 8 | 2 |\\n| 2 | Add cache hit/miss metrics to TenantKeyManager | functionality | 3 | 7 | 1 |\\n| 3 | Audit credential deletion and access operations | code_quality | 2 | 9 | 2 |\\n| 4 | Add error handling to maintainCache() timer | code_quality | 1 | 7 | 1 |\\n| 5 | Expose credential file gauge and cleanup metrics | functionality | 2 | 6 | 1 |\\n\\n### Key observations:\\n\\n- **Biggest gap**: Credential deletion and access leave no audit trail despite audit infrastructure already existing - only creation is logged (idea #3, highest impact)\\n- **Silent failure risk**: `maintainCache()` in TenantKeyManager has no try/catch around its async work - a single failed derivation causes an unobserved promise rejection (idea #4, easiest fix)\\n- **Unused abstraction**: `DecryptionError` class exists in crypto.ts with rich context fields but `decrypt()` never uses it - raw crypto errors propagate instead (idea #1)\\n- **Invisible metrics**: Bo